  "narrative": "DRIVER\nUSD leads D1 CSM at 100 in a Risk-Off High regime with Fed rate hike repricing and rising US 10Y yields to 4.595 driving the bid. USDCAD is the cleanest expression with D1 momentum at 72 accelerating, CADJPY H4 CSM diverging 59 points above D1 confirming CAD cross-buying, and GBPUSD offers the highest-conviction short given GBP at D1 CSM 0 with GBPJPY correlation at 0.93 amplifying any GBP weakness. AUD H4 CSM fading hard at 0 versus D1 at 60 is the critical short-term flag \u2014 AUDUSD and AUDJPY downside is accelerating intraday faster than daily structure implies.\n\nMOMENTUM\nGaining: USDCAD CMP 64, D1 72 rising sharply with H4 66 confirming trend alignment across both timeframes\nFading: GBPUSD CMP 31 D1 and H4 both collapsing, AUDUSD CMP 41 H4 at 14 in freefall, NZDUSD CMP 43 H4 at 21 accelerating lower\n\nWATCH\nVIX continuation above 20 triggers further S&P 500 selling, pushing USDJPY higher as yen safe-haven buying fails against USD dominance\nWTI Oil reversal from 103.10 drop deepens, hitting USDCAD topside as CAD commodity link reasserts through USDCAD correlation with AUDUSD at -0.61\nUS 2Y yield breakout above 3.60 reprices Fed expectations, accelerating GBPUSD toward next support as GBP CSM holds zero",
